While several models are available for genomic predictions, their similarities have been reported in previous studies (Heslot et al. 2012; Rutkoski et al. 2012; Juliana et al. 2017b). So, we used only the genomic best linear unbiased prediction (GBLUP) model with the genomic relationship matrix (G-matrix) calculated from markers (VanRaden 2008). The GBLUP model was implemented in the ‘R’ package BGLR (Pérez and de los Campos 2014) and can be represented as,4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
